<paragraph id="9E53D157FFCAFFFCD9FDD016338AFEDF" blockId="1.[151,1436,227,321]" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">
Basionym: 
<taxonomicName id="59ECAAD4FFCAFFFCD87FD0163081FEBF" authority="A. Juss. " box="[277,422,266,289]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Boraginaceae</taxonomicName>
subfam. 
<taxonomicName id="59ECAAD4FFCAFFFCDB7BD016350DFEBF" authority="Retief &amp; A. E. van Wyk (2005: 79)" authorityName="Retief &amp; A. E. van Wyk" authorityPageNumber="79" authorityYear="2005" box="[529,1066,266,289]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Codonoideae">Codonoideae Retief &amp; A.E.van Wyk (2005: 79)</taxonomicName>
. — 
<typeStatus id="41576FF5FFCAFFFCDD3FD01635AAFEBF" box="[1109,1165,266,289]" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">Type</typeStatus>
: 
<taxonomicName id="59ECAAD4FFCAFFFCDDF0D01635C6FEBF" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" box="[1178,1249,266,289]" class="Insecta" family="Codonaceae" genus="Codon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AC980D45FFCAFFFCDDF0D01635C6FEBF" box="[1178,1249,266,289]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">Codon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., generic 
<typeStatus id="41576FF5FFCAFFFCDC04D01634BBFEBF" box="[1390,1436,266,289]" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="59ECAAD4FFCAFFFCD848D036338EFEDF" authority="(Linnaeus 1767: 292)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityPageNumber="292" baseAuthorityYear="1767" box="[290,681,298,321]" class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Codon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="royenii">
<emphasis id="AC980D45FFCAFFFCD848D036309DFEDF" box="[290,442,298,321]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">Codon royenii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="FA7DACA6FFCAFFFCD8ADD0363386FEDF" author="Linnaeus, C." box="[455,673,298,321]" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" refId="ref2943" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1767) Systema Naturae per regna tria naturae, 12 ed., Vol. 2. Stockholm, L. Salvius. 736 pp." type="book" year="1767">Linnaeus 1767: 292</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9E53D157FFCAFFFCD9FDD06D31DDFC4C" blockId="1.[151,1436,369,1171]" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">
Subperennial or perennial, densely branched, spiny shrublets. Strong taproot present. Stems terete, erect. Indumentum of white spines consisting of 3–12 cystolithic foot cells, stiff, unicellular trichomes and 2–5- celled, uniseriate, gland-tipped trichomes. Leaves alternate, estipulate, entire, petiolate, petioles stiffly curved towards shoot apex and lamina held +/- parallel to shoot axis, lamina (narrowly) ovate with acuminate apex and rounded base, margin entire to coarsely serrate, adaxially densely spiny, abaxially with spines only on the very prominent midvein, venation pinnate with lateral veins ascending. Inflorescence frondose-bracteose, initially scorpioid, later straight monochasia, rarely reduced to a single terminal flower. Flowers erect, with 10–20 perianth elements, actinomorphic, bisexual, hypogynous. Calyx divided nearly to base, calyx lobes unequal in width, narrow and wide calyx lobes alternating, densely spinose and pubescent. Corolla white or yellow, sympetalous, campanulate to saucer-shaped, lobes half-erect to spreading, oblong with rounded apex, inside with 6–10 flap-like protrusions near filament bases. Stamens 6–10, filaments basally pubescent, epipetalous, inserted ca. 1/5 
<superScript id="69997C1FFFCAFFFCD88ED20630D6FCB6" attach="left" box="[484,497,794,808]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">th</superScript>
from the base of the tube, incurved and closing the tube near base, then erect, anthers dorsifix, exserted. Ovary bicarpellate, nearly two-locular by deeply intruding placentae, style terminal, divided into two long stigmatic lobes for ca 1/2 of its length. Fruit a dry, bivalved capsule, loculicidal, seeds numerous, ellipsoidal to ovoidal, testa with deeply reticulate epidermis cells. Endosperm copious.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D6F682DCFFCAFFFCD9ACD2C3321CFB0D" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph id="9E53D157FFCAFFFCD9ACD2C3321CFB0D" blockId="1.[151,1436,369,1171]" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">
This new family consist only of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="59ECAAD4FFCAFFFCDBABD2C33228FC66" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" box="[705,783,991,1016]" class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Codon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AC980D45FFCAFFFCDBABD2C33228FC66" box="[705,783,991,1016]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">Codon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with two species, 
<taxonomicName id="59ECAAD4FFCAFFFCDA87D2C334BBFC67" authority="Schinz (1884: 173)" authorityName="Schinz" authorityPageNumber="173" authorityYear="1884" box="[1005,1436,991,1017]" class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Codon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schenckii">
<emphasis id="AC980D45FFCAFFFCDA87D2C33596FC66" box="[1005,1201,991,1016]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">Codon schenckii</emphasis>
Schinz (1884: 173)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="59ECAAD4FFCAFFFCD9A1D51A3368FB81" authority="Linnaeus (1767: 292)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityPageNumber="292" authorityYear="1767" box="[203,591,1029,1055]" class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Codon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="royenii">
<emphasis id="AC980D45FFCAFFFCD9A1D51A3064FB81" box="[203,323,1030,1055]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">C. royenii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FA7DACA6FFCAFFFCD821D5193368FB81" author="Linnaeus, C." box="[331,591,1029,1055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" refId="ref2943" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1767) Systema Naturae per regna tria naturae, 12 ed., Vol. 2. Stockholm, L. Salvius. 736 pp." type="book" year="1767">Linnaeus (1767: 292)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="E6FB91C7FFCAFFFCDB12D519326DFB81" box="[632,842,1029,1055]" name="Namibia" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">Southwest Africa</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry id="E6FB91C7FFCAFFFCDA31D51935A9FB81" box="[859,1166,1029,1055]" name="South Africa" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">Republic of South Africa</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="E6FB91C7FFCAFFFCDDA1D519341FFB81" box="[1227,1336,1029,1055]" name="Namibia" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">Namibia</collectingCountry>
). 
<taxonomicName id="59ECAAD4FFCAFFFCDC26D51A31CAFBDB" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Codon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="royenii">
<emphasis id="AC980D45FFCAFFFCDC26D51A31CAFBDB" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">Codon royenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been typified by 
<bibRefCitation id="FA7DACA6FFCAFFFCD891D53033CFFBD8" author="Jarvis, C. E. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Allan, D. M. &amp; Reveal, J. L." box="[507,744,1068,1094]" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 100" refId="ref2895" refString="Jarvis, C. E., Barrie, F. R., Allan, D. M. &amp; Reveal, J. L. (1993) A list of Linnaean generic names and their types. Regnum Vegetabile 127: 1 - 100." type="journal article" year="1993">
Jarvis 
<emphasis id="AC980D45FFCAFFFCDB26D53033ADFBDB" box="[588,650,1068,1093]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
(1993)
</bibRefCitation>
, but for 
<taxonomicName id="59ECAAD4FFCAFFFCDA3ED5303507FBDB" authorityName="Schinz" authorityYear="1884" box="[852,1056,1068,1093]" class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Codon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schenckii">
<emphasis id="AC980D45FFCAFFFCDA3ED5303507FBDB" box="[852,1056,1068,1093]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">Codon schenckii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
several 
<typeStatus id="41576FF5FFCAFFFCDDE0D53035D2FBD8" box="[1162,1269,1068,1094]" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">syntypes</typeStatus>
are available (
<bibRefCitation id="FA7DACA6FFCAFFFCD9F5D54E3335FBF2" author="Friedrich-Holzhammer, M." box="[159,530,1106,1132]" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" refId="ref2746" refString="Friedrich-Holzhammer, M. (1967 b) 118. Hydrophyllaceae. Prodromus einer Flora von Sudwestafrika, Lieferung 13. J. Cramer, Germany. 2 pp." type="book" year="1967">Friedrich-Holzhammer 1967b</bibRefCitation>
). A recent, critical revision of the genus is not available, only the cursory treatment in 
<bibRefCitation id="FA7DACA6FFCAFFFCD841D56533BAFB0D" author="Friedrich-Holzhammer, M." box="[299,669,1145,1171]" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" refId="ref2746" refString="Friedrich-Holzhammer, M. (1967 b) 118. Hydrophyllaceae. Prodromus einer Flora von Sudwestafrika, Lieferung 13. J. Cramer, Germany. 2 pp." type="book" year="1967">Friedrich-Holzhammer (1967b)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<collectingCountry id="E6FB91C7FFCAFFFCDBA4D5653210FB0D" box="[718,823,1145,1171]" name="Namibia" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">Namibia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
